<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include('partials/html-head'); -%>

  <body>
    <div id="app" class="wrap">
      <%- include('partials/header'); -%>
        <h1 class="page-title">privacy</h1>

        <section>
          <p>
            At Pinggy, your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect
            your
            information when you use our services.
          </p>

          <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
          <p>When you create an account and use Pinggy, we collect the following information:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Username:</strong> Required for account creation and identification.</li>
            <li><strong>Password:</strong> Encrypted and stored securely to protect your account.</li>
            <li><strong>Email Address:</strong> Used for account verification, communication, and recovery.</li>
            <li><strong>Subscribed Feeds/Channels:</strong> To provide you with your personalized feed.</li>
            <li><strong>Saved Bookmarks:</strong> To allow you to save and access content you want to revisit.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Provide and maintain the Pinggy service.</li>
            <li>Enable you to manage your subscriptions and bookmarks.</li>
            <li>Improve the functionality and user experience of Pinggy.</li>
            <li>Communicate with you regarding updates, support, or feedback.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Analytics</h2>
          <p>
            We use <strong>Cabin Analytics</strong> to collect anonymous usage data. This helps us understand how users
            interact with Pinggy and improve the service. Cabin Analytics does not track personal information or user
            identities.
          </p>

          <h2>How We Protect Your Information</h2>
          <p>We take data security seriously and implement the following measures to protect your information:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Passwords are securely hashed and cannot be viewed by anyone, including us.</li>
            <li>Your data is stored on secure servers with industry-standard encryption.</li>
            <li>Access to your information is restricted to authorized personnel only.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Third-Party Sharing</h2>
          <p>Pinggy does <strong>not</strong> share, sell, or rent your personal information with any third parties.</p>

          <h2>Your Rights</h2>
          <p>You have full control over your data. You can:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Update your account information.</li>
            <li>Delete your saved bookmarks or subscriptions at any time.</li>
            <li>
              Request account deletion by contacting us at <a href="mailto:support@pinggy.com">support@pinggy.com</a>.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Data Retention</h2>
          <p>
            We retain your information for as long as your account is active. If you delete your account, we will remove
            all associated data from our servers.
          </p>

          <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected on this page, and we
            encourage you to review it regularly.
          </p>

          <h2>Contact Us</h2>
          <p>If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:</p>
          <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@pinggy.com">support@pinggy.com</a></p>
        </section>
    </div>
    <%- include('partials/footer'); -%>
  </body>

</html>